		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p113024">XV-11 bumper design and climbing</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=113024&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c#p113024"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21080&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c">craigbla</a></strong> &raquo; January 11th, 2013, 5:58 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I tried adding 3/8&quot; shims under the speaker stands that Neato is climbing up on but it still was not enough.<br /><br />When I look at the bumper from the side it seems that there is enough vertical play in the bumper to allow it to ride up on objects(especially with rounded edges) more than I would like.  Neato is hitting a low price point so I understand that there are limits to what they can do but I think it would help it they could reduce the vertical play in the bumper so it would engage more often and not ride up objects as much.</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile113024">
			<dt>
				<a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21080&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c">craigbla</a>
