			<h3 ><a href="#p113929">Re: XV-11 bumper design and climbing</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=113929&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c#p113929"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19808&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c">glnc222</a></strong> &raquo; February 10th, 2013, 5:49 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content"><span style="font-weight: bold">All Wire, Plastic-Free Version</span><br />Thinner 18-20 guage wire or any metal bendable into bearing mounts -- paper clips -- for thicker steel bumper extension bail; duck tape on.  On <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/cgi-bin/jump/jump.cgi?21" class="th23autolinks postlink" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">ebay</a> you can see coat hanger wire even used for art work.  Also available <a href="http://www.robotreviews.com/cgi-bin/jump/jump.cgi?26" class="th23autolinks postlink" onclick="this.target='_blank';" rel="nofollow">Amazon</a>.</div>

			
