		</div><br /><div class="inline-attachment">
		<dl class="thumbnail">
			<dt><a href="./download/file.php?id=5765&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c&amp;mode=view"><img src="./download/file.php?id=5765&amp;t=1&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c" alt="plasticattach.jpg" title="plasticattach.jpg (22.27 KiB) Viewed 3710 times" /></a></dt>
			<dd> bottom view bumper side, flange removed</dd>
		</dl>
		</div><br />[edit] actually the left side of the screw post is better than right side with arrow shown.  Note side of bumper will move inwards flush with the block, and to the left when hit on the front of the vacuum.  3/4&quot; forwards of the back edge of the bumper is the best pivot position, will be behind the post.<br /><br /><br />A pivot can be glued to the outside without drilling the case, protruding a bit compared to countersunk flathead screws.  Pivot at height where back curve of front begins as top rotates back, bottom out slightly, for snug fit to front.</div>

			
				<div class="notice">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19808&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c">glnc222</a> on April 1st, 2013, 2:39 pm, edited 1 time in total.
					
				</div>
			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile114567">
			<dt>
				<a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=19808&amp;sid=db14c9b53ecaf4bdb4905ec94b2a1e1c">glnc222</a>
